Find Longest Continuous Growth Period
A stock analytics system in Chennai records daily stock price changes (as integers). The analyst wants to find the longest streak of consecutive increasing values (regardless of order in input).

Given an unsorted integer array nums, find:

the length of the longest consecutive sequence

Input format :
First line: integer n
Second line: n space-separated integers
Output format :
Print a single integer → length of longest consecutive sequence
Code constraints :
0 <= n <= 10^5

-10^9 <= nums[i] <= 10^9

Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
6
100 4 200 1 3 2
Output 1 :
4
Input 2 :
10
0 3 7 2 5 8 4 6 0 1
Output 2 :
9


Solution:


#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;


int main(){
    
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    
    vector<int>arr(n);
    
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        cin>>arr[i];
    }
    
   unordered_set<int>s(arr.begin(),arr.end());
   
   int longest = 0;
   
   for(int x:s){
       if(s.find(x-1) == s.end()){
           int current = x;
           int length = 1;
           
           while(s.find(current+1) != s.end()){
               length++;
               current++;
           }
       longest = max(longest,length);
       
       }
   }
   
   cout<<longest;
}
